messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full HTTP request path:
- /printshops/stats

All HTTP methods acceptable:
- false

Methods accepted (based on the code):
- HEAD: false
- POST: false
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- The getPrintShopStatistics method is annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/printshops/stats", method = RequestMethod.GET) (see ManagerController#getPrintShopStatistics). There is no class-level @RequestMapping in ManagerController, so the full path is exactly the method-level value: /printshops/stats.
- The method attribute explicitly specifies RequestMethod.GET, so only GET is declared in the code. Following the instruction to judge acceptance "based on the code, not on experiential assumptions", only GET is marked true; other HTTP methods are not present in the annotation and therefore marked false.
- Note: Although some frameworks/servers can implicitly handle HEAD or OPTIONS for GET handlers at runtime, those behaviors are not reflected as explicit method acceptances in the source code and were therefore treated as false per the task instructions.
